Cliffjumper finished mending his foot, he cried out in pain one last
time. "Man I wish Beachcomber was with us." He then turned to Torca.
"That's Caliburst, a Decepticon." he said through gritted teeth, "That
ship we saw must be full, lets take a better look." he suggested, as he
hobbled towards the hill.

Caliburst roled onto his side. There was no real dammage, he was just
shaken up. He thought back, <I've never seen that other Autobot> but he
knew it didnt matter. He was outguned, and outnumbered. He rolled onto
his side, and grabbed his gun, and stood up. He tried his best not to
show his fear, and glanced out of the corner of his eye at Slusglinger.
<He's just sitting there, for all I know he's dead, and I am in a world
of trouble> he thought, as he rushed up to the hill, hoping to catch the
autobots before they ascended it.
